            <title>Lower Costs through Green HVAC</title>
            <description>&lt;p&gt;
	For years, environmentalists have been pushing for changes to heating, ventilation and air-conditioning (HVAC) standards, hoping to make them less harmful for the environment. While creating a safer environment is great, in the business world, money talks.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
	If you own a business, a large chunk of your business dollar is probably going to heating and cooling. However, there are many actions you can take to not only make your building&amp;#39;s heating and cooling systems more eco-friendly and energy efficient but also save you money.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
	Any time you can lessen the load on your HVAC system while maintaining the building&amp;#39;s internal temperature will obviously save you some dough, but it isn&amp;#39;t all about the machinery. There are things you can do &amp;mdash; or encourage your tenants to do &amp;mdash; beyond&amp;nbsp;&lt;a href="http://www.grainger.com/category/hvac-and-refrigeration/ecatalog/N-k00"&gt;HVAC maintenance&lt;/a&gt;&amp;nbsp;to get more ecological benefit from your money while managing your energy costs.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
	Many of these actions, along with some pertinent information about energy use in general, are outlined in the following infographic. Read through them and consider how you might make a few changes to help businesses save the world as well as their bottom line.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
	&lt;img alt="" src="http://media.noria.com/sites/Uploads/2014/1/29/3ca7a9bb-d871-45e9-9d95-6b8fb235f9a6_Energy-Costs-Infographic-2.jpeg" style="width: 640px; height: 3095px;" /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/noria/reliableplant/tags/HVAC/~4/M1gzCdDpYH4" height="1" width="1" alt=""/&gt;</description>
            <a10:updated>2014-01-29T14:17:24-06:00</a10:updated>
